sch:rule.sch:report:
@resp and
                                    @source can not be used
                                    together

@resp or
                                    @source is expected for
                                div[@type='translation']

Only
                                    @reason is mandatory in
                                div[@type='translation']

sch:rule.sch:assert:
Gap with the attribute
                                    @unit="component" can only be used inside seg with the
                                    @type="component".

Space can't have @quantity and @unit attributes with
                                    @type='binding-hole' or @type='descender' or @type='ascender',
                                    the only @type possible is
                                @type='defect'.

@match='..'
                                    and @locus='name' always work
                            together

The attributes
                                    @from-custom and @to-custom must be used
                                together

sch:rule.sch:report:
for milestone using the attribut
                                   @unit, the attribute @n is
                               mandatory

sch:rule.sch:assert:
@type='ref' can
                                    only be used inside the translation part of the
                                    edition

@type='ref' requires the
                                    use of @unit="stanza" or
                                @unit="line'

sch:rule.sch:report:
@n
                                    is mandatory with
                            milestone/@type="ref"

sch:rule.sch:assert:
For @type="settlement", the @subtype should be one of the
                                    following values: @subtype='town' or @subtype='village' or
                                    @subtype='hamlet' or @subtype='armyCamp' or
                                    @subtype='undetermined' or
                                @subtype='establishment'

For @type="builtPlace", the @subtype should be one of the
                                    following values: @subtype='temple' or @subtype='monastery' or
                                    @subtype='feedingHall' or @subtype='pavillion' or
                                    @subtype='undetermined'

For @type="cultivation", the @subtype should be one of the
                                    following values: @subtype='garden' or @subtype='field' or
                                    @subtype='fieldPaddy' or @subtype='fieldMillet' or
                                    @subtype='orchard' or @subtype='orchardAreca' or
                                    @subtype='orchardCitrus' or @subtype='fieldIrrigated' or
                                    @subtype='fieldDry' or @subtype='fieldSalted' or
                                    @subtype='undetermined' or
                                @subtype='nursery'

For @type="hydrographic", the @subtype should be one of the
                                    following values: @subtype='tank' or @subtype='river' or
                                    @subtype='pond' or @subtype='canal' or @subtype='undetermined'
                                    or @subtype='wetland' or @sutype='pool' or
                                    @subtype='lake'

For @type="naturalPlace", the @subtype should be one of the
                                    following values: @subtype='forest' or @subtype='wood' or
                                    @subtype='grove' or @subtype='tree' or @subtype='mountain' or
                                    @subtype='undetermined' or
                                @subtype='mount'

with the
                                   @type="fortnight", you should used either @subtype="dark" or
                                   @subtype="bright".

With the
                                    @type='season', you can only use one of the following values:
                                    hemanta, grisma, varsa.

With the
                                    @type='equinox', you can only use one of the following values:
                                    autumn or spring.
